HEADWORD: Self-centred
<hw>Self`-cen"tred</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Centered in itself, or in
one's self.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There hangs the ball of earth and water mixt,⟦br⟧
<qex>Self-centered</qex> and unmoved.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>interested solely or primiarily in oneself, or one's
own welfare; disinclined to consider the interests of others; selfish;
egotistical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-centring</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Self-centering</ent>⟦br⟧
